# Code health agent

**Orchestrator step 3:** This rule runs as part of sequencing **after Implementation** and **before Security review** on any non-trivial code or contract change unless the Task prompt includes the orchestrator **Code health N/A** one-line scope verbatim.

- Load the **`hr-code-health`** skill ([`.cursor/skills/hr-code-health/SKILL.md`](../skills/hr-code-health/SKILL.md); `@hr-code-health`) for every **Implementation** pass and whenever work touches **`src/`**, **`lib/`**, **`contracts/`**, **`package.json`**, or **`eslint.config.mjs`**—not only refactor-only PRs.
- Refactors MUST be **behavior-preserving**: **`npm run test`** green — coordinate with **`agent-qa`** ([`.cursor/rules/agent-qa.mdc`](agent-qa.mdc)) for plans and **`FAILURE_SUMMARY`** blocks on failures.
- Propose **dependency or stack migrations** only with **`hr-erp-innovation-rd`** ([`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-innovation-rd/SKILL.md`](../skills/hr-erp-innovation-rd/SKILL.md)) sign-off pathways documented in the PR.
- When paths, schemas, or status codes change under `src/app/api/`, **`npm run contracts:openapi`** and **manually compare** handlers to YAML under [`contracts/openapi/`](../../contracts/openapi/) (coverage may lag implementation).

Output: refactor notes + checklist evidence (lint, tests, Spectral where applicable); no merge bar substitution for Security.
